Assignment 1 – EC2 Web Server Deployment

What I Built:

I deployed a web server on an Amazon EC2 instance inside a custom VPC.

The setup included:

- Custom VPC
- Public subnet
- Internet Gateway
- Route table with internet access (0.0.0.0/0 → IGW)
- One EC2 instance (Amazon Linux)
- Security Group allowing HTTP (port 80)
- Web server installed using user data

The EC2 instance successfully served a web page when accessed via its public IP address.

What I Learned:

- How VPC networking works (subnets, route tables, Internet Gateway).
- Difference between public and private subnets.
- How security groups control inbound and outbound traffic.
- How to automate EC2 configuration using user data scripts.
- How traffic flows from the internet to an EC2 instance.
- This assignment strengthened my understanding of AWS networking fundamentals.

Challenges & Solutions:

1. Website not loading.
Cause: Port 80 not allowed in Security Group.
Fix: Added HTTP (80) inbound rule from 0.0.0.0/0

2. No internet connectivity.
Cause: Missing route to Internet Gateway.
Fix: Added 0.0.0.0/0 route and associated route table with subnet.

3. User data script not working.
Cause: Incorrect setup commands.
Fix: Corrected script to install and start Apache automatically.

Outcome:
Successfully deployed a working EC2 web server with proper networking and security configuration. 
This forms the foundation for more advanced AWS architectures like Load Balancers and Auto Scaling.
